# Hooks and Utilities Guide

This project uses custom hooks and utility functions to handle common functionality.

## Custom Hooks
The project uses several custom hooks to encapsulate reusable logic:

- [src/hooks/useGitHubProjects.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useGitHubProjects.ts) - Fetches and manages GitHub project data
- [src/hooks/useIsMobile.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useIsMobile.ts) - Detects mobile viewport for responsive behavior
- [src/hooks/useLazyLoadSection.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useLazyLoadSection.ts) - Implements lazy loading for sections
- [src/hooks/useScrollAnimation.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useScrollAnimation.ts) - Manages scroll-based animations

## Utility Functions
- [src/utils/animations.ts](mdc:src/utils/animations.ts) - Contains animation utility functions and configuration

## Services
- [src/services/github.ts](mdc:src/services/github.ts) - Service for interacting with GitHub API

## TypeScript Types
- [src/types/github.ts](mdc:src/types/github.ts) - Type definitions for GitHub API data
